\title{Catcolab Decapodes}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{version}{1.0.0}

\meta{description}{CatColab Decapodes - Discrete Exterior Calculus for PDE modeling on meshes via Decapodes.jl integration. Model physics equations compositionally with automatic code generation.}

\subtree{
\title{CatColab Decapodes: Discrete Exterior Calculus}
\p{\strong{Trit}: -1 (MINUS - validator/verifier) \strong{Color}: Purple (#8A2BE2)}

\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Decapodes in CatColab enable \strong{Discrete Exterior Calculus (DEC)} for modeling PDEs:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Differential forms}: 0-forms (scalars), 1-forms (vectors), 2-forms (flux)}
\li{\strong{Operators}: d (exterior derivative), ★ (Hodge star), Δ (Laplacian)}
\li{\strong{Multiphysics}: Compose PDEs from different domains}
\li{\strong{Automatic code generation}: Export to AlgebraicJulia/Decapodes.jl}
}

\p{This is CatColab's most advanced logic, connecting category theory to numerical PDE simulation.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Mathematical Foundation}
\p{Discrete Exterior Calculus discretizes differential geometry on meshes:}

\pre{\startverb
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              DISCRETE EXTERIOR CALCULUS              │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Spaces (Differential Forms):                        │
│    Ω⁰ (0-forms): Scalars on vertices (temperature)  │
│    Ω¹ (1-forms): Vectors on edges (velocity)        │
│    Ω² (2-forms): Flux through faces (flow rate)     │
│                                                      │
│  Operators:                                          │
│    d: Ωᵏ → Ωᵏ⁺¹  (exterior derivative)              │
│    ★: Ωᵏ → Ωⁿ⁻ᵏ  (Hodge star)                       │
│    δ = ★d★: Ωᵏ → Ωᵏ⁻¹ (codifferential)              │
│    Δ = dδ + δd: Laplacian                           │
│                                                      │
│  De Rham Complex:                                    │
│    Ω⁰ ──d──► Ω¹ ──d──► Ω² ──d──► Ω³                 │
│     │         │         │         │                  │
│     ★         ★         ★         ★                  │
│     ▼         ▼         ▼         ▼                  │
│    Ω³ ◄──d── Ω² ◄──d── Ω¹ ◄──d── Ω⁰                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Double Theory}
\pre{\startverb
// DEC double theory (simplified)
pub fn th_decapodes() -> DiscreteDblTheory {
    let mut cat = FpCategory::new();

    // Form spaces
    cat.add_ob_generator(name("Form0"));  // Scalars
    cat.add_ob_generator(name("Form1"));  // 1-forms
    cat.add_ob_generator(name("Form2"));  // 2-forms

    // Differential operators
    cat.add_mor_generator(name("d0"), name("Form0"), name("Form1"));
    cat.add_mor_generator(name("d1"), name("Form1"), name("Form2"));

    // Hodge star
    cat.add_mor_generator(name("star0"), name("Form0"), name("Form2"));
    cat.add_mor_generator(name("star1"), name("Form1"), name("Form1"));
    cat.add_mor_generator(name("star2"), name("Form2"), name("Form0"));

    // Constraint: d ∘ d = 0
    cat.add_equation(
        compose(name("d0"), name("d1")),
        zero_morphism(name("Form0"), name("Form2"))
    );

    cat.into()
}
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{CatColab Implementation}
\subtree{
\title{Form Space Declaration}
\pre{\startverb
{
  "type": "ObDecl",
  "name": "Temperature",
  "theory_type": "Form0",
  "description": "scalar temperature field on vertices"
}
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Operator Declaration}
\pre{\startverb
{
  "type": "MorDecl",
  "name": "gradient_T",
  "dom": "Temperature",
  "cod": "HeatFlux",
  "theory_type": "d0",
  "description": "gradient of temperature"
}
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{PDE Declaration}
\pre{\startverb
{
  "type": "EqDecl",
  "name": "heat_equation",
  "equation": "∂T/∂t = κ·Δ(T)",
  "description": "heat diffusion equation"
}
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Physics Examples}
\subtree{
\title{Example 1: Heat Equation}
\pre{\startverb
∂T/∂t = κ·ΔT

Where:
  T: Form0 (temperature)
  κ: diffusivity constant
  Δ = ★d★d (Laplace-Beltrami)

CatColab composition:
  T ──d──► dT ──★──► ★dT ──d──► d★dT ──★──► ★d★dT = ΔT
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example 2: Navier-Stokes (2D)}
\pre{\startverb
∂ω/∂t + (v·∇)ω = ν·Δω

Where:
  ω: Form2 (vorticity)
  v: Form1 (velocity)
  ν: viscosity

Composition:
  Advection: v ──∧──► v∧ω (wedge product)
  Diffusion: ω ──Δ──► Δω
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example 3: Maxwell's Equations}
\pre{\startverb
dE = -∂B/∂t    (Faraday)
dB = 0         (no monopoles)
δE = ρ/ε₀     (Gauss)
δB = μ₀J + μ₀ε₀∂E/∂t  (Ampère-Maxwell)

Where:
  E: Form1 (electric field)
  B: Form2 (magnetic field)
  J: Form1 (current density)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example 4: Shallow Water Equations}
\pre{\startverb
∂h/∂t + ∇·(hv) = 0         (continuity)
∂v/∂t + (v·∇)v = -g∇h      (momentum)

Where:
  h: Form0 (water height)
  v: Form1 (velocity)
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Multiphysics Composition}
\p{Decapodes compose via \strong{operad algebras}:}

\pre{\startverb
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              MULTIPHYSICS COMPOSITION                │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Physics 1: Heat Transfer                            │
│    ∂T/∂t = κ·ΔT                                      │
│                                                      │
│  Physics 2: Advection                                │
│    ∂c/∂t = -v·∇c                                     │
│                                                      │
│  Composed: Advection-Diffusion                       │
│    ∂c/∂t = κ·Δc - v·∇c                               │
│                                                      │
│  Interface: Shared Form1 velocity v                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{CatColab 0.2 Integration}
\p{CatColab 0.2 (Wren) introduced Decapodes integration:}

\pre{\startverb
// Export to Decapodes.jl
const analysis = await model.analyze({
  type: "decapodes-export",
  mesh: "sphere_mesh.obj",
  time_span: [0, 100],
  parameters: { κ: 0.1 }
});

// Returns animated solution visualization
\stopverb}
}

